text.section:
Actions for which the Commission may charge a fee include:
an initial tariff or tariff change;
a certificate of public convenience and necessity;
an application to provide or abandon service;
a preparation of any record in appeal;
a certification of any document;
an application or petition to increase or decrease rates;
an annual report;
a copy of papers, testimony, microfiche, records, and computer printouts; and
any other filing or service for which the Commission reasonably determines that a fee is required.
